Reduced Fuel Moisture Content (FMC) changes all parameters in Equations (2) and (3) for the worse regarding the fire development [ 8]. The lower latent heat of vaporization (
L V
) is the main contributor. Drying prior to ignition therefore exerts a major influence on the characteristics of wildland fires as well as compartment fires. Understanding the drying processes is therefore necessary in order to understand fire development and fire severity in dry conditions.
